==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-leverage.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A [[force]] [[compounded]] by means of a [[lever]] rotating around a pivot; see [[torque]].
#:''A crowbar uses '''leverage''' to pry nails out of wood.''
# By extension, any [[influence]] which is compounded or used to gain an [[advantage]].
#:''Try using competitors' prices for '''leverage''' in the negotiation.''

===Transitive verb===
[[Category:English buzzwords]]
[[Category:English transitive verbs]]
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|leverag|e|}}

# To [[use]]; to gain advantage; to take full advantage of an existing thing.
#:''They plan to '''leverage''' the publicity they gained.''

====Usage notes====
Use as a verb is still predominantly a [[buzzword]], primarily among American English speakers.

